  "body": "```\r\neip: 2270\r\ntitle: Generate Ethereum account from Digital ID\r\nauthor: Jon Ramvi <jon@blockchangers.com>\r\nstatus: Draft\r\ntype: Standards Track\r\ncategory Core\r\ncreated: 2019-09-09\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Simple Summary\r\nGeneration of Ethereum accounts from solutions for personal electronic ID for secure identification (Digital ID). This is one solution for solving recoverability. \r\n\r\n## Abstract\r\nMany countries offer Digital ID to their citizens. Sweden and Norway have BankID. Denmark has NEM ID, Finland has TUPAS, the Netherlands has DigiD and Estonia has a Digital ID. These solutions are OpenID Connect (OIDC) implementations returning\r\n\r\n1. true if the user is who she claims to be\r\n2. some data fields about the user\r\n\r\nThis standard is a proposal for what goes into generating a seed for an Ethereum account so that it \r\n\r\n1. is recoverable \r\n2. has a high enough entropy to be secure\r\n\r\nBy adding together a mixture of parameters the seed should only be recoverable by the user, and no third party.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nMany people are afraid of losing their mnemonic key. Having an Ethereum account connected to your Digital ID makes it so that you can always recover your funds.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n\r\nDo a sha256 of 3 parameters concatenated:\r\n* The the Digital ID GUID e.g. `sub` for BankID Norway [something only the digital ID provider knows]\r\n* Take the user's social security number [not really confidential, but not always known and adds to the seed's entropy]\r\n* Take a user-generated password [something only the users knows]\r\n\r\nSeed = `sha256([sub][ssn][password])`\r\n\r\nThis can be used directly as an Ethereum private key\r\n\r\n### Increased security\r\n\r\nMany of the Digital ID providers also provide signing. Send the Seed for signing with the Digital ID and use the returned data as the Ethereum key.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/).",
