    "body": "My 2 cents on this:\r\n- On 1st case: UID and SS number being considered as public, this is the same as using the password with some public salt. With respect to guessing attack, the password is really a weak point\r\n- on 2nd case: it has some advantages (leveraging the authentication to your digital ID provider to get access to the signing function) but means also that you trust your ID provider while providing the seed for being signed. Additionally a signature is not necessarily deterministic (it won't be the case for the common schemes, e.g. default version of ECDSA, DSA, RSA-PSS are not) so it might not work.",
